#Creating Time Series

ts_data <- ts(Spotify_Quarterly_Revenue$Revenue,start=c(2017,1), frequency=4)
ts_data
##      Qtr1 Qtr2 Qtr3 Qtr4
## 2017  902 1007 1032 1449
## 2018 1139 1273 1352 1495
## 2019 1511 1667 1731 1855
## 2020 1848 1889 1975 2168
## 2021 2147 2331 2501 2689
## 2022 2661 2864 3036 3166
## 2023 3042
attributes(ts_data)
## $tsp
## [1] 2017 2023    4
## 
## $class
## [1] "ts"
plot(ts_data)

#Taking mean of data
mean_forecast <- meanf(ts_data,3)
plot(mean_forecast)

# Naive
naive_forecast <- naive(ts_data,3)
plot(naive_forecast)

attributes(naive_forecast)
## $names
##  [1] "method"    "model"     "lambda"    "x"         "fitted"    "residuals"
##  [7] "series"    "mean"      "level"     "lower"     "upper"    
## 
## $class
## [1] "forecast"
# Random Walk
rwf_forecast <- rwf(ts_data,3)
plot(rwf_forecast)

rwf_forecast <- rwf(ts_data,3, drift=TRUE)
plot(rwf_forecast)

# Seasonal Naive
snaive_forecast <- snaive(ts_data,3)
plot(snaive_forecast)

# Moving Averages
MA5_forecast <- ma(ts_data,order=5)
plot(MA5_forecast)

MA9_forecast <- ma(ts_data,order=9)
plot(MA9_forecast)

# Plot all in a single chart
plot(mean_forecast)
lines(naive_forecast$mean,col="red")
lines(rwf_forecast$mean,col="blue")
lines(snaive_forecast$mean,col="green")
lines(MA5_forecast,col="yellow")
lines(MA9_forecast,col="pink")

# Decomposition
